On Tue, 8 May 2007, Billy Price wrote:

> Go in the winter time.

I drove the length of Death Valley a couple years ago, in a rental car but
it was October and the temps still exceeded 100F by quite a few degrees
for most of the day. it is about 200 miles if I recall from Scottys Castle
to the town at the South end, and the only services were at the park
service headquarters area.

> Seriously, experienced desert people routinely die there because they
> under/over estimate Death Valley/themselves
> .
> Get online with the NPS, follow all the local rangers' suggestions.
>
> Be prepared for a multi-day hike out if the bus dies.

Amen!

